A `while` loop runs code *conditionally*. It evaluates a condition before each iteration, and loops as long as the condition remains true.

```rust
let mut number = 3;

while number != 0 {
    println!("{}!", number);
    number -= 1;
}
println!("LIFTOFF!");
```

